According to a report by Intel Market Research, the China Polyester Fiber Textile Market was valued at USD 48.75 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 68.32 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion due to China's highly integrated manufacturing ecosystem, rising domestic consumption, booming e-commerce sector, and growing global demand for affordable, durable, and recyclable textile products. Continuous advancements in recycled polyester (rPET), functional fibers, high-performance textiles, and smart textile technologies are further accelerating market growth while supporting China's transition toward sustainable and innovation-driven textile manufacturing.
